Operations

  • SEND

    Operation IDproduct_updated

    Available only on servers:

    • redis

    Accepts the following message:

    Details of the product that has been updated
    Message IDproduct_updated
    object
    timestamp
    integer

    The Unix epoch time when this update took place

      Examples values:
    • 1234567890
    code
    string

    The code of the product that was updated

      Examples values:
    • "3017620420009"
    rev
    integer

    The revision number for the change

      Examples values:
    • 194
    product_type
    string

    The high-level type product, e.g. "food", "beauty", "petfood"

      Allowed values:
    • "food"
    • "beauty"
    • "petfood"
    • "product"
    flavor
    deprecated
    string

    DEPRECATED: The product_type field should be used to identify the kind of product this event relates to. The Product Opener application type that generated the message, e.g. off, opff, off-pro

      Allowed values:
    • "off"
    • "opff"
    • "obf"
    • "opf"
    • "off-pro"
    user_id
    string

    The public facing user id of the user that made the edit

    action
    string

    The nature of the change, e.g. "created", "deleted"

      Allowed values:
    • "updated"
    • "created"
    • "deleted"
    • "archived"
    • "unarchived"
    • "reprocessed"
    comment
    string

    Overview of the change, provided by the user

    object

    Lists of field names that were changed

      Examples values:
    • {"fields":{"change":["categories"]}}
    object
    array<string>

  • RECEIVE

    Operation IDuser-registered

    Available only on servers:

    • redis

    Accepts the following message:

    Details of a new user that has registered with the app
    Message IDuser-registered
    object
    id
    string

    The internal Keycloak id of the new user

    email
    string

    The user's email address

    userName
    string

    The user's public facing user name (user id)

    name
    string

    The user's display / full name

    locale
    string

    Preferred 2 letter language code

      Examples values:
    • "fr"
    country
    string

    2 letter country code or "world"

      Examples values:
    • "fr"
    • "world"
    realm
    string

    The Keycloak realm in which the user was created

    Const:"openfoodfacts"
    clientId
    string

    The client_id of the application that initiated the new user registration process

      Examples values:
    • "OFF"
    newsletter
    string

    Present if the user subscribed to the newsletter

    Const:"subscribe"
    requestedOrg
    string

    The producer organization the user has requested to join

    Additional properties are allowed.

    Examples

    {
  "id": "string",
  "email": "string",
  "userName": "string",
  "name": "string",
  "locale": "fr",
  "country": "fr",
  "realm": "openfoodfacts",
  "clientId": "OFF",
  "newsletter": "subscribe",
  "requestedOrg": "string"
}
    This example has been generated automatically.

  • RECEIVE

    Operation IDuser-deleted

    Available only on servers:

    • redis

    Accepts the following message:

    Generated when a user requests to be forgotten
    Message IDuser-deleted
    object
    id
    string

    The internal Keycloak id of the user

    email
    string

    The user's email address

    userName
    string

    The user's public facing user name

    realm
    string

    The Keycloak realm

    Const:"openfoodfacts"
    newUserName
    string

    A randomly generated alias for the user that will be associated with their historic contributions

      Examples values:
    • "anonymous-1234"

    Additional properties are allowed.

    Examples

    {
  "id": "string",
  "email": "string",
  "userName": "string",
  "realm": "openfoodfacts",
  "newUserName": "anonymous-1234"
}
